rComments: The textbook for this course was an absolute godsend. Although Professor Bao is clearly interested in her field, her poor grasp of English and heavy accent made it extremely difficult for her to explain concepts or answer questions. The course also required understanding of mathematics and electromagnetism well beyond the indicated prerequisites.

Absolute worst prof I've had in 5 years at this University. Doesn't even show up to lectures and barely showed up for the final exam. Exam content was not even close to what was studied in class or assignments. Equation sheet for the final was useless since the content was completely different.

The exam this semester was on material we never saw before. After many questions she started writing the equations we never saw before on the board. Obviously no one knew what the equations meant. + the English of the exam was a disaster. The words were placed not where they should be, typos everywhere, weird sentence structure. Worst exam ever.

Avoid this prof if you can. She is impossible to understand in class, and expects you to understand math above your level. However, marking on exams tends to be fair. Most things I learned in this class, I learned from the internet or the textbook.
Excellent industry relevant course on Fiber Optic technology. Very well lectured and most course content was from professors personal experience. Well conducted and informative.
Lectures consisted of her copying equations from the book onto the board.  Brutal final.  This class was a hugely disappointing waste of time.

Well, can't really understand her. Her english is kinda bad and she really has trouble working through simple problems in class. Didn't really go to lectures, but the exam wasn't on stuff that was on the assignments. She gave us all decent marks though.
